## Screen Spec Protocol

### When to Write

| Condition | Screen Spec Required |
|-----------|---------------------|
| Epic includes UI | ✅ Required |
| Epic is backend only | ❌ Not required |
| Modifying existing screen | ✅ Changed parts only |

### Authoring Order

```
1. Epic Spec finalized (PO approved)
2. Story breakdown complete
3. Write screen spec (use templates/screen-spec.md)
4. Validate handoff checklist
5. Dev team handoff
```

### Quality Criteria

Service-planner level of detail:
- **ASCII art** for layout visualization
- All elements have explicit **specs (size, color, behavior)**
- **State-based UI branches** defined (loading, empty, error)
- **Policy tables** for business rules

### Storage Location

```
sprints/s{N}/design/{Epic-ID}-screen-spec.md

Example: sprints/s52/design/E-10-screen-spec.md
```

### 7-Level Structure

| Level | Content | Required |
|-------|---------|----------|
| Level 1 | Full IA & entry points | ✅ |
| Level 2 | Main screen (layout) | ✅ |
| Level 3 | Component details | ✅ |
| Level 4 | Modals & dialogs | If applicable |
| Level 5 | External integrations | If applicable |
| Level 6 | State-based UI | ✅ |
| Level 7 | Policy summary | ✅ |

### Linking to Stories

After completion, add screen spec links to all stories in the Epic:

```markdown
## References
| Source | Path/Link | Referenced Section |
|--------|----------|-------------------|
| **Screen Spec** | [design/E-XX-screen-spec.md](../design/E-XX-screen-spec.md) | Level 2, 3 |
```

